These changes let you write methods for KVO accessing using natural Ruby syntax:

class T
kvo_array :squares do
 def size
   10
 end
 def [](i)
   i * i
 end
end
end

>> T.new.valueForKey('squares')
=> [0, 1, 4, 9, 16, 25, 36, 49, 64, 81]

commit_list.message:
Revision 95: Minor optimizations concerning IP version detection and
local/connected address. As a side effect, a newly accepted incoming
socket can now be queried for its local/connected address from within
the onSocket:didAcceptNewSocket: delegate method.  Whereas before, one
had to wait until onSocket:didConnectToHost:port:.
